Package: libmuxaudio0
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Audio multiplexing library with side-channel support
 MuxAudio is a C library for multiplexing audio streams with side-channel
 data (such as speech events, visemes, word boundaries) using LEB128 framing.
 .
 This package contains the shared library.

Package: libmuxaudio-dev
Section: libdevel
Architecture: any
Depends: libmuxaudio0 (= ${binary:Version}),
         ${misc:Depends},
         libogg-dev,
         libvorbis-dev,
         libopus-dev,
         libflac-dev,
         libmpg123-dev,
         libmp3lame-dev,
         libfdk-aac-dev
Description: Audio multiplexing library - development files
 MuxAudio is a C library for multiplexing audio streams with side-channel
 data (such as speech events, visemes, word boundaries) using LEB128 framing.
 .
 This package contains the development files (headers and static library).

Package: muxaudio-tools
Architecture: any
Depends: libmuxaudio0 (= ${binary:Version}),
         ${shlibs:Depends},
         ${misc:Depends}
Description: Audio multiplexing tools
 MuxAudio is a C library for multiplexing audio streams with side-channel
 data (such as speech events, visemes, word boundaries) using LEB128 framing.
 .
 This package contains command-line tools:
  * mux - Encode audio from stdin with side channel data from fd 3
  * demux - Decode multiplexed stream to audio and side channel data
